The paper deals with the problem of maintaining statistic aggregates over a data stream, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses lower bounds and algorithms for approximating sums and counting 1's, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions memory consumption and succinct algorithms, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
